<c74object name='sp.triggeralign~' category='' module='SP-Tools'>
    <digest>Trigger alignment based on descriptor analysis latency
</digest>
    <description>Trigger alignment based on descriptor analysis latency.
</description>
    <discussion><h4><openfilelink filename="SP-Tools Overview.maxpat">Open the Overview Patch</openfilelink></h4>
The <o>sp.triggeralign~</o> object takes a gate input and time-aligns it to any message-based input in the left inlet. This is primarily useful for delaying triggers/gates so they line up with non-deterministic processes like descriptor analysis or corpus queries.
</discussion>

	<metadatalist>
		<metadata name='author'>Rodrigo Constanzo, Flucoma Project</metadata>
